Siaya County aspirant for governor&#39;s seat William Oduol has stated that he is in ODM party to stay.Oduol said he only decamped to National Agenda Party of Kenya (NAP-K) after he was short-changed in the 2013 ODM party nominations. &quot;Our house was leaking and I decided to seek refuge in the neighbourhood but since the roof has been repaired, I have every reason to be back,&quot; Oduol said.Oduol was speaking at Rarieda Secondary School on Wednesday. He also said should Rasanga fairly beat them in the nominations, he would support him.Oduol decamped from ODM in the last elections and joined NAPK after what he termed nominations skewed to benefit his rivals. ALSO READ: CORD rejects planned review of elections law